TY  - JOUR
T1  - Separable Markovian Decision Problems
AU  - Denardo, Eric V.
Y1  - 1968/03/01
PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.14.7.451
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.14.7.451
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 451
EP  - 462
VL  - 14
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The special structure of a class of Markovian decision problems is exploited to simplify the determination of optimum policies. For certain pairs consisting of a state i and decision k, the cost cki separates (cki = ai + bk), while the transition probabilities pkij and transition time distributions Fkij are independent of i. Equivalence of a second Markovian decision problem which exploits this structure is demonstrated for the discounted and averaging cases. In addition, streamlined approaches are presented for dealing directly with the original problem, and a particular inventory model is further simplified.
AB  - The special structure of a class of Markovian decision problems is exploited to simplify the determination of optimum policies. For certain pairs consisting of a state i and decision k, the cost cki separates (cki = ai + bk), while the transition probabilities pkij and transition time distributions Fkij are independent of i. Equivalence of a second Markovian decision problem which exploits this structure is demonstrated for the discounted and averaging cases. In addition, streamlined approaches are presented for dealing directly with the original problem, and a particular inventory model is further simplified.
